      • getNumberFilesSkipped

        long getNumberFilesSkipped()
        Returns the number of files being skipped from scanning. Files are skippped if:

        • the file is flagged for deletion but does not exist in the stream
        • the file belong to a component that does not exist in the stream
        • the file associated to a language definition that does not have any scanners
        Returns:
        the number of files being skipped from scanning.

      • setNumberFilesSkipped

        Parameters:
